# CyberChef Guide

## What is CyberChef

CyberChef is a free browser-based tool made by GCHQ (UK intelligence agency) for encoding, decoding, encrypting, decrypting, compressing, and analysing data. It requires no installation and runs entirely in your browser.

**Link:** [gchq.github.io/CyberChef](https://gchq.github.io/CyberChef)

It is an essential tool for CTF challenges and day-to-day security work.

---

## Interface Overview

| Section | Purpose |
|---------|---------|
| Operations (left sidebar) | All available functions |
| Recipe (middle-left) | Chain of operations to apply |
| Input (top-right) | Data you paste or upload |
| Output (bottom-right) | Result after applying the recipe |

**Recipe** is the key concept — you chain multiple operations together and CyberChef applies them in order.

---

## The Magic Operation

The single most useful button in CyberChef.

Drag **Magic** into the recipe and paste your data. CyberChef will automatically detect the encoding and decode it for you.

Great for when you get an unknown blob of text in a CTF and have no idea what encoding it is.

